The '''Risco Waterfall''' ("Risco" meaning risk in English) is a group of waterfalls located in Rabaçal, [[Paul da Serra]], in the [[Madeira Islands]].

The [[waterfall]] is 100m high, consisting of a group of different water streams coming vertically down the mountainside. At its foot there are rocks covered in small plants and a small natural pool.<ref>
